  "text": "HomeNewsDeals on EVs include new models from Chevrolet and Honda with lease payments under $300 through October.With a week left in October, now's the time to snag an EV lease with monthly payments under $300.New EVs are popular to lease rather than own outright because most qualify for a federal tax credit that isn't always available to buyers. That might be why Edmunds data found almost 80% of new electric purchases are now leased, as of mid October. The lease \"loophole\" offers up to $7,500 off. To find the best leases, CarsDirect, an automotive research firm, compiled lease terms through Oct. 31. We sorted through the best prices for all-electric options. Costs maybe vary based on your location and lease terms can inflate monthly costs.From highest to lowest monthly cost, here are the best EV lease deals for October.Tesla Model 3. Tesla2024 Tesla Model 3 Long Range RWD Monthly Payment: $299True Monthly Cost: $410Term Length: 36 monthsDue at Signing: $3,999Range: 363 milesSticker price: $42,4902024 Subaru Solterra. Subaru2024 Subaru Solterra PremiumMonthly Payment: $279True Monthly Cost: $286Term Length: 36 monthsDue at Signing: $279Range: 227 milesSticker price: $44,9952024 Honda Prologue.Honda2024 Honda Prologue EX Monthly Payment: $259True Monthly Cost: $295Term Length: 36 monthsDue at Signing: $1,299Range: Up to 296 milesSticker price: $47,4002024 Nissan Leaf.Nissan2024 Nissan Leaf SMonthly Payment: $249True Monthly Cost: $322Term Length: 36 monthsDue at Signing: $2,649Range: 150 milesSticker price: $28,1402024 Chevrolet Equinox EV.Chevy2024 Chevrolet Equinox EV 2LTMonthly Payment: $239True Monthly Cost: $365Term Length: 24 monthsDue at Signing: $3,029Range: 300 milesSticker price: $41,9002024 Toyota bZ4X XLE.Toyota2024 Toyota bZ4X XLEMonthly Payment: $269True Monthly Cost: $325Term Length: 36 monthsDue at Signing: $1,999Range: Up to 252 milesSticker price: $43,070The bZ4X deal is available longer than the others through Nov. 4.2024 Hyundai Kona Electric.Hyundai2024 Hyundai Kona Electric SELMonthly Payment: $199True Monthly Cost: $365Term Length: 24 monthsDue at Signing: $3,999Range: Up to 261 milesSticker price: $36,675For 2024 trims, the SE is available for $179 per month, while the top trim Limited is $249 under the same terms.2024 Hyundai Ioniq 5.Hyundai2024 Hyundai Ioniq 5 SEL RWDMonthly Payment: $199True Monthly Cost: $365 Term Length: 24 monthsDue at Signing: $3,999Range: 303 milesSticker price: $47,400The base SE Standard Range with the same terms is $159 per month, while the SE is $189. 2024 Fiat 500e Inspi(RED).Stellantis2024 Fiat 500e Inspi(RED)Monthly Payment: $199True Monthly Cost: $275Term Length: 36 monthsDue at Signing: $2,669Range: Up to 149 milesSticker price: $34,0952024 VinFast VF 82024 VinFast VF 8 EcoMonthly Payment: $199True Monthly Cost: $225Term Length: 36 monthsDue at Signing: $894Range: 264 milesSticker price: $46,0552024 Kia EV6.Kia2024 Kia EV6 Light Long Range RWDMonthly Payment: $179True Monthly Cost: $345Term Length: 24 monthsDue at Signing: $3,999Range: 310 milesSticker price: $45,950With a 36-month deal the same EV6 bumps to $229 per month.2024 Kia Niro EV.Kia2024 Kia Niro EV WindMonthly Payment: $169True Monthly Cost: $335Term Length: 24 monthsDue at Signing: $3,999Range: 253 milesSticker price: $39,600A 36-month term for the same Niro EV Wind pushes the monthly payment to $219 per month. 2024 Hyundai Ioniq 6 SE.Hyundai2024 Hyundai Ioniq 6 SE RWD Standard RangeMonthly Payment: $159True Monthly Cost: $325Term Length: 24 monthsDue at Signing: $3,999Range: 240 milesSticker price: $37,5002024 Volkswagen ID.4Volkswagen2024 Volkswagen ID.4 S Monthly Payment: $99True Monthly Cost: $265Term Length: 36 monthsDue at Signing: $5,995Range: 206 milesSticker price: $44,855Final thoughtsBig names in the EV space are looking attractive in October with affordable monthly pricing. The all-new Honda Prologue is on offer and the Hyundai Ioniq 6 has one of the best deals available on the base trim. Volkswagen is running a lease special on the ID.4 S model. Before committing to an EV, double check the range and battery specs. It's not as great of a deal if you'll be constantly charging.",
